==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cad
<hw>Cad</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Abbrev. fr.
<ets>cadet</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A person who stands at the
door of an omnibus to open and shut it, and to receive fares; an idle
hanger-on about innyards.</def> <mark>[Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Dickens.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A lowbred, presuming person; a mean, vulgar
fellow.</def> <mark>[Cant]</mark> <rj><au>Thackeray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>cadaster</ent>⟦br⟧
